But then when we try to complete this, as this code is trying to finish completion, it's

00:30:05.119 --> 00:30:10.199
going to lock. And that means this is good while you're working with in a single user

00:30:10.199 --> 00:30:15.160
environment, right? Like you don't want to cache a table and, you know, like then work

00:30:15.160 --> 00:30:16.800
with something that hasn't finished caching.

00:30:17.400 --> 00:30:19.400
So this is this is good behavior that we want.

00:30:20.000 --> 00:30:24.280
